text: RT @framednetwork: Is it possible for a photographer to make more than 4 million dollars a year?

paraphrases.text: How much do photographers make per year? More than 4 million dollars?
How much do photographers get paid on average?
Can you make more than 4 million dollars a year as a photographer?

qpairs.question: What kind of photographers are there and how much do they get paid?
qpairs.answer:
Good ones
bad ones
average ones

Good ones with good business sense and contacts make the most.

Do you know anything at all about photography or wedding photography specifically?
Since you are asking this question then I doubt it so you will probably fall into the middle category above and make peanuts or be out of business in weeks.

Being a successful photographer in any field means having the necessary skills and knowledge and this takes time to learn.
qpairs.simplified_answer: Good ones with good business sense or contacts. In any field this needs a lot of skills and knowledge that can take time to learn.
qpairs.summarized_answer: The best photographers are those with a lot of skills and knowledge, with good business sense or contacts.

qpairs.question: How much does a photographer make per year?
qpairs.answer: According to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, as of May 2008, photographers had a mean hourly wage of $17.14 and a mean annual wage of $35,640. The lowest 10 percent made $8.14 per hour or $16,920 annually, while the highest made $30.02 per hour or $62,430 annually.
qpairs.simplified_answer: According to the Bureau of Labor, as of May 2008, photographers had a mean hourly wage of $17.14 and a mean annual wage of $35,640.
qpairs.summarized_answer: According to the Bureau of Labor, as of May 2008, photographers had a mean hourly wage of $17.14 and a mean annual wage of $35,640.
